Facemasks are not Respiratory Protection

 Facemasks by design do not seal tightly to the wearers face

 Therefore they allow unfiltered air to easily flow around the sides of the facemask

into the breathing zone and respiratory tract of the wearer

In addition the materials used for facemasks are not regulated for their ability to

filter particles and are known to vary greatly between models

This makes it possible for small particles to pass through or around the facemask

and be inhaled by the wearer
